                android:text="1. Prepare the Sushi Rice:

Rinse the sushi rice under cold water until the water runs clear.

Combine rice and water in a rice cooker. Cook according to the rice cooker instructions.

While the rice is still hot, gently fold in the mixture of rice vinegar, sugar, and salt. Allow the rice to cool to room temperature.

2. Prepare the Spicy Tuna Filling:

In a bowl, combine diced tuna, mayonnaise, Sriracha sauce, soy sauce, sesame oil, and chopped green onion. Mix well.

Adjust the spiciness and seasoning according to your taste preferences.

3. Assemble the Spicy Tuna Roll:

Lay a bamboo sushi rolling mat on a flat surface. Place a sheet of plastic wrap on top of the mat.

Lay a sheet of nori, shiny side down, on the plastic wrap.

Wet your hands and grab a handful of sushi rice. Spread the rice evenly over the nori, leaving about half an inch of nori at the top edge.

Place a line of the spicy tuna filling horizontally across the center of the rice.

Add cucumber and avocado slices next to the tuna.

Start rolling the nori and rice over the filling using the bamboo mat. Apply gentle pressure to shape the roll.

Once you reach the exposed nori at the top, wet the edge with a bit of water and seal the roll.

Using a sharp knife, wet it to prevent sticking and slice the roll into bite-sized pieces.

4. Serve:

Arrange the Spicy Tuna Rolls on a plate.

Serve with soy sauce for dipping.

Optionally, serve with pickled ginger and wasabi on the side."
